<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[168,776,1636,1926]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">
<emphasis inLineHeading="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,316,1700,1724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">Hyperlopha crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
in general fascia, even though is slightly larger. 
<taxonomicName box="[168,304,1767,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[168,304,1767,1791]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">H. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a new species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway JD" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" pagination="1 - 529" refId="ref11463" refString="Holloway JD (2005) The moths of Borneo (parts 15 &amp; 16): family Noctuidae, subfamily Catocalinae. The Malayan Nature Journal 58: 1 - 529." type="journal article" year="2005">Holloway (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. He differentiated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker sensu Holloway" authorityYear="1976" box="[535,672,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristifera">
<emphasis box="[535,672,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">H. cristifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">H. crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the male genitalia. We have collected only female specimen of 
<emphasis box="[447,585,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker sensu Holloway" authorityYear="1976" box="[447,581,1868,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperlopha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="1117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristifera">H. cristifera</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
More research is needed for this species.
</paragraph>
